{
  "_comment": [
    "gosec config — use with: gosec -conf .gosec ./...",
    "",
    "Suppressions are handled inline with '// #nosec Gxxx' annotations.",
    "Rules suppressed and why:",
    "  G204 — subprocess launched with variable:",
    "          reconkit intentionally wraps external tools (nmap, httpx,",
    "          subfinder, dnsx, eyewitness). exec.CommandContext with",
    "          separate args prevents shell injection.",
    "  G304 — file path from taint input:",
    "          paths are either internally generated (scan/report output",
    "          dirs assembled with filepath.Join) or explicit CLI args,",
    "          which is normal behaviour for a CLI tool.",
    "  G703 — path traversal via taint analysis:",
    "          destination paths are assembled from controlled base dirs;",
    "          no user-controlled path components reach os.WriteFile.",
    "  G104 — errors unhandled:",
    "          fixed: all tmp.Close() and rows.Close() calls now use '_ ='."
  ],
  "global": {
    "audit": "false"
  }
}
